## Tabular benchmarking

Tabular-FM evaluation is many small (estimator × OpenML task × fold) cells, not one big run — and cells are cached on disk (exca), keyed to the estimator config **and the code version**:

```bash
# One cell (typed estimator configs — see ESTIMATORS in benchmark.py)
uv run python src/{{ package_name }}/benchmark.py estimator=mlp estimator.hidden_dim=64 task_id=31 fold=0

# Full grid — locally, or as a SLURM array (edit the grid in the script)
bash scripts/run_benchmark.sh
sbatch scripts/sbatch_benchmark.sh

# Per-dataset table, mean ranks, win rates + paired Wilcoxon vs a baseline
uv run python scripts/aggregate_benchmark.py outputs/benchmark_<stamp> --baseline logreg

# Foundation-model baselines (TabPFN weights: non-commercial research only)
uv sync --extra tabular-baselines
uv run python src/{{ package_name }}/benchmark.py estimator=tabpfn
```

Re-running a grid recomputes only missing or code-changed cells; `utils/codever.py` auto-bumps the cache version on semantic code edits and writes a diff changelog to `cache/benchmark/code_versions/CHANGELOG.md`.

Ship your own models behind the sklearn interface (`src/{{ package_name }}/sklearn_wrapper.py`) — that's how TabPFN/TabICL get adopted, and it makes them drop-ins for this harness and everyone else's.

